body:
# Please help if you can reproduce this locally, or in production!

Making this issue so that I remember to fix this. See e.g. [here](http://www.rust-ci.org/huonw/unicode_names/doc/unicode_names/) for an example (happens in Firefox latest stable, but not IE11).

I'm having trouble fixing this, because I can't reproduce it locally. Maybe rust-ci is doing something custom somewhere?

Issue is probably in this function at line 767 of `src/librustdoc/html/static/main.js`, which gets copied verbatim to `doc/main.js` when you build. 

```
    $(function() {
        var toggle = "<a href='javascript:void(0)'"
            + "class='collapse-toggle'>[<span class='inner'>-</span>]</a>";

        $(".method").each(function() {
           if ($(this).next().is(".docblock")) {
               $(this).children().first().after(toggle);
           }
        });

        var mainToggle = $(toggle);
        mainToggle.append("<span class='toggle-label' style='display:none'>"
            + "&nbsp;Expand&nbsp;description</span></a>")
        var wrapper =  $("<div class='toggle-wrapper'>");
        wrapper.append(mainToggle);
        $("#main > .docblock").before(wrapper);
    });
```

Of note is that this line:

```
+ "&nbsp;Expand&nbsp;description</span></a>")
```

Has an incorrect trailing `</a>`. I also try to add `display:none` directly to the html string, which maybe something somwhere is mad about. I propose the following refactor as a possible shot-in-the-dark fix.

```
    $(function() {
        var toggle = "<a href='javascript:void(0)'"
            + "class='collapse-toggle'>[<span class='inner'>-</span>]</a>";

        $(".method").each(function() {
           if ($(this).next().is(".docblock")) {
               $(this).children().first().after(toggle);
           }
        });

        var mainToggle = $(toggle);
        var toggleLabel  =  $("<span class='toggle-label'>&nbsp;Expand&nbsp;description</span>");
        mainToggle.append(toggleLabel);
        var wrapper =  $("<div class='toggle-wrapper'>");
        wrapper.append(mainToggle);
        $("#main > .docblock").before(wrapper);
        $(".toggle-label").hide();
    });
```

If you have a build that has this bug, I would request that you try this patch on the generated `doc/main.js` file, and see if it fixes it.
